A week after UK actor Idris Elba announced testing positive for Covid-19, his wife Sabrina Dhowre's also tested positive. The model and actres announced her status on Oprah Winfrey's new show, Oprah Talks Covid-19. Oprah interviewed the couple, who got married last April, through Facetime. According to CNN, Sabrina wasn't surprised to test positive, because she was with Idris and he was also infected. Read: MANDELA GRANDSON TESTS POSITIVE FOR CORONAVIRUS She also said she feels fine. "It might change in the coming weeks and we'll keep everyone updated, but it is worrisome that we're sitting here, two people and we're asymptomatic." Read: WEDDING BELLS FOR LERATO AND THAMI Like millions of people all over the world, I've been staying safer at home for over a week now. I know a lot of people are feeling stressed, overwhelmed, and uncertain. Because of that, I wanted to offer some hope and gather thought leaders and people going through it to add some perspective. Which is why I FaceTimed Idris Elba and his wife Sabrina who are safely quarantined together after he tested positive for COVID-19. Idris fills me in on his journey and Sabrina reveals the result of her test after they decided to quarantine together. Tap the link in my bio to watch our conversation for FREE on the Apple TV app (on your phone) or visit apple.co/oprahtalks A post shared by  Oprah (@oprah) on Mar 21, 2020 at 7:19pm PDT  When Idris posted a live video on Twitter, announcing the news of his Covid-19 status, Sabrina was next to him and people were attacking her for sitting next to him while he was infected. Idris said it was weird that people were criticising her for being with him. People on Twitter shared their thoughts about Sabrina's announcement.   If I'm being honest, I would only leave my husband to be in quarantine alone, if there are kids involved. I'm naturally a care giver, so i find the Sabrina and Idris Situation normal.                       